input: The cat needs the cow. The cat needs the lion. The cow is nice. The cow visits the lion. The dog does not visit the cat. The dog visits the lion. The lion sees the cow. If something sees the cow and the cow sees the lion then it is nice. If something is young and nice then it sees the cat. If something sees the dog and it sees the cow then it is green. If something needs the cow and it does not need the lion then the lion is blue. If something sees the lion and it visits the lion then the lion visits the cow. All nice things are young. If something sees the cat and the cat needs the cow then the cat is nice. If the cat is not nice then the cat is not blue. Question: The cat does not see the cat.?

universe u

constant obj : Type u

constant Cat : obj
constant Cow : obj
constant Lion : obj
constant Dog : obj

constant Nice : obj → Prop
constant Visits : obj → obj → Prop
constant Sees : obj → obj → Prop
constant Young : obj → Prop
constant Green : obj → Prop
constant Blue : obj → Prop
constant Needs : obj → obj → Prop

axiom T1 : Needs Cat Cow
axiom T2 : Needs Cat Lion
axiom T3 : Nice Cow
axiom T4 : Visits Cow Lion
axiom T5 : ¬ Visits Dog Cat
axiom T6 : Visits Dog Lion
axiom T7 : Sees Lion Cow

axiom R1 : ∀ x : obj, Sees x Cow ∧ Sees Cow Lion → Nice x
axiom R2 : ∀ x : obj, Young x ∧ Nice x → Sees x Cat
axiom R3 : ∀ x : obj, Sees x Dog ∧ Sees x Cow → Green x
axiom R4 : ∀ x : obj, Needs x Cow ∧ ¬ Needs x Lion → Blue Lion
axiom R5 : ∀ x : obj, Sees x Lion ∧ Visits x Lion → Visits Lion Cow
axiom R6 : ∀ x : obj, Nice x → Young x
axiom R7 : ∀ x : obj, Sees x Cat ∧ Needs Cat Cow → Nice Cat
axiom R8 : ¬ Nice Cat → ¬ Blue Cat

theorem cat_does_not_see_cat : ¬ Sees Cat Cat :=
begin
  sorry
end

theorem cat_sees_cat : Sees Cat Cat :=
begin
  apply R2,
  split,
  apply R6,
  apply R7,
  split,
  exact T1,
  exact T1,
end
